2.00	Barbara_Montgomery_(actress)	Barbara Montgomery	Barbara Montgomery (born June 25, 1939) is an American television and film actress. Montgomery is best known for her role as Cassietta Hetebrink on the sitcom, Amen, Montgomery played the role for four years, and left in 1990. She later starred in the short-lived ABC program Married People as Olivia Williams, and also appeared on many shows such as A Different World, The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air, Disneyland, and Living Single.	
